HEADWORD: Dimorph
<hw>Di"morph`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ two-formed;
<grk>di`s-</grk> twice (see <er>Di-</er>) + <grk>morfh`</grk>
form.]</ety> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Either one of the two forms
of a dimorphous substance; <as>as, calcite and aragonite are
<ex>dimorphs</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

